				\begin{document}$$ {}_{15}q_{45}^{t + n} - {}_{15}q_{45}^{t} = \alpha + \beta \left( {ss} \right) + \varepsilon . $$\end{document}</tex-math></disp-formula>Table&#xA0;<xref rid="Tab2" ref-type="table">2</xref> presents results of two OLS regression models considering mortality change first over a 5-year period and then over a 10-year period. In each case we regress observed mortality changes in four age ranges on the state socialist dummy variable across countries and years, as shown in Table&#xA0;<xref rid="Tab2" ref-type="table">2</xref>.<table-wrap id="Tab2"><label>Table&#xA0;2</label><caption><p>State socialist/market capitalist dichotomy predicts mortality changes</p></caption><table frame="hsides" rules="groups"><thead><tr><th align="left"/><th align="left">Intercept</th><th align="left">&#x3B2; (state socialist)</th><th align="left">&#x3C3;<sub>&#x3B2;</sub></th><th align="left"><italic>t</italic> (&#x3B2;)</th><th align="left">Pr&#xA0;&gt;&#xA0;<italic>t</italic></th><th align="left">Adjusted <italic>R</italic><sup>2</sup></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td align="left" colspan="7">Five-year change-score regression for <sub>15</sub>q<sub>45</sub> (<italic>n</italic>&#xA0;=&#xA0;107)</td></tr><tr><td align="left">&#xA0;&#x394;(<sub>15</sub>q<sub>15</sub>)</td><td char="." align="char">&#x2212;0.00013</td><td char="." align="char">&#x2212;0.00009</td><td char="." align="char">9.44E&#x2212;05</td><td char="." align="char">&#x2212;0.99</td><td char="." align="char">0.322</td><td char="." align="char">&#x2212;0.0001</td></tr><tr><td align="left">&#xA0;&#x394;(<sub>15</sub>q<sub>30</sub>)</td><td char="." align="char">&#x2212;0.00034</td><td char="." align="char">0.00039</td><td char="." align="char">0.000225</td><td char="." align="char">1.74</td><td char="." align="char">0.085</td><td char="." align="char">0.0185</td></tr><tr><td align="left">&#xA0;&#x394;(<sub>15</sub>q<sub>45</sub>)</td><td char="." align="char">&#x2212;0.00138</td><td char="." align="char">0